      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:1:37:9",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " كُلُّ شَيْ‏ءٍ يَطِيرُ فَلَا بَأْسَ بِبَوْلِهِ وَ خُرْئِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Abdullah Bin Al Mugheira, from Jameel Bin Darraj, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Everything which flies, so there is no problem with its urine and its droppings’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "9. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ’Abd Allah ibn af-Mughirah from Jamil ibn Darraj from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Urine and droppings of the things that fly are not harmful.”’ "
        ]
      }
